{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians --> | name = Gerry And The Crocodettes | background = group_or_band | origin = [[New Zealand]] | genre = [[Children's music]] | years_active = 2007–present | website = [http://thecrocodettes.com Official website] | current_members = [[Gerry Drummond]] }} '''Gerry And The Crocodettes''' are a space themed [[children's music|children's musical group]] formed in [[New Zealand]] in 2006 by Gerry Holmes (now Gerry Drummond).<ref>Van Dijk, Marion. [http://www.stuff.co.nz/nelson-mail/news/508309 "Space adventure taking off"], ''[[Nelson Mail]]'', Nelson, 27 June 2008. Retrieved on 2010-07-12.</ref> The group is led by Gerry Drummond and currently also consists of the characters, Frincess (a frog princess), Herman (a [[yeti]]), Pat the Alligator and two Star Fairies, Venus and Saturn.<ref>Crocodettes tale out of this world, [[The Northern Advocate]], 22 January 2010</ref>
==Storyline== According to their website, the storyline of Gerry And The Crocodettes is that all of the characters apart from Herman came to earth from a place called Croco Galaxy. Herman is a yeti from [[Tibet]] that Pat befriended when he came to [[earth]].
==Concerts== The group perform live concerts for children at venues throughout New Zealand. Their live concerts feature original songs and dances woven with educational messages.<ref>Cowdrey, Alice. [http://www.stuff.co.nz/nelson-mail/entertainment/2579140/Family-Croco-festival "Family Croco festival"], ''[[Nelson Mail]]'', Nelson, 9 July 2009. Retrieved on 2010-07-13.</ref> They have been described as "New Zealand's answer to [[The Wiggles]]"<ref>Adams, Julia. Gerry and the Crocodettes, KiaOra - [[Air New Zealand]] inflight magazine, January 2010</ref>
==Recordings== Gerry And The Crocodettes have released a CD (2008) and a DVD (2009), both titled "Gerry And The Crocodettes" and are releasing a Christmas CD in 2010 titled "Christmas With The Crocodettes".
