The '''North Carolina Comedy Arts Festival''' is an annual comedy festival in [[Carrboro, North Carolina|Carrboro]], [[North Carolina]], United States.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indyweek.com/gyrobase/Content?oid=oid%3A409563|title=The North Carolina Comedy Arts Festival expands to a month for its 10th anniversary|last=Smith|first=Zack |date=3 February 2010  |work=Independent Weekly|accessdate=13 February 2010}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newsobserver.com/life/story/308137.html|title=N.C. Comedy Arts Festival aims to teach you a thing or two|last=Menconi |first=  David |date= January 29, 2010 |work=News & Observer|accessdate=13 February 2010|location=Raleigh, North Carolina}}</ref>

The festival was started in 2001 by Zach Ward (of [[Dirty South Improv Comedy Theater]]) as an improv showcase and improv seminars. The festival has grown year over year. In 2009 it added stand up comedy and in 2010 expanded to include sketch comedy and film as well as extending into a month-long festival in Carrboro, North Carolina.

