{{Expand French|Rendez vous (groupe)|date=June 2018}} {{Infobox musical artist | name = Rendez-Vous | background = group_or_band | image = RendezVousMachine.jpg | image_size = | landscape = | alt = | caption = Rendez-Vous performs at Machine du Moulin Rouge in Paris | alias = | origin = [[Paris]], [[France]] | genre = [[Post-Punk]], [[new wave]] | years_active = {{start date|2012}}–present | label = Zappruder Records, AVANT! Records | associated_acts = | website = {{URL|http://rendezvousrendezvous.com/}} | current_members = {{Unbulleted list|Francis Mallari|Elliot Berthault|Maxime Gendre|Simon Dubourg|Guillaume Rottier}} }}
'''Rendez-Vous''' is a [[post-punk]] French band from [[Paris]], [[France]], formed in 2012.
== History == Rendez-Vous was founded in 2012 by Francis Mallari and Elliot Bethault. A few months later, they added Maxime Gendre and Simon Dubourg.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lesinrocks.com/lesinrockslab/news/2014/12/decouverte-du-lab-89-rendez/|title=La découverte du lab #89 : Rendez-Vous|work=Les Inrocks|access-date=2018-06-04|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref name=":1" /> The band released their first EP in 2014, ''Rendez-Vous'', for [[Zappruder Records]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://noisey.vice.com/da/article/rzvak9/check-out-this-new-video-by-french-synthpunk-band-rendez-vous|title=Check Out This New Video By French Synthpunk Band Rendez-Vous|date=2015-04-29|work=Noisey|access-date=2018-06-04|language=da}}</ref>
The band start touring across Europe in the summer of 2015.<ref name=":0" />
In 2016, Rendez-Vous released a second EP, ''Distance'', mixed by [[Ben Greenberg]] from [[The Men (punk band)|The Men]],<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/musique/2016/12/08/03006-20161208ARTFIG00092-rendez-vous-le-groupe-francais-qui-remet-le-post-punk-au-gout-du-jour.php|title=Rendez-vous, le groupe français qui remet le post-punk au goût du jour|date=2016-12-08|work=FIGARO|access-date=2018-06-04|language=fr-FR}}</ref> for their new label [[Avant Records|AVANT! Records]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thefourohfive.com/music/review/rendez-vous-distance-ep-145|title=Rendez-Vous - Distance EP|work=The 405|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en}}</ref> The self-titled single "Distance" was included in [[Les Inrockuptibles]] magazine's "100 best songs of the year".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lesinrocks.com/2016/12/06/musique/2016-les-100-meilleurs-morceaux-de-lannee-des-inrocks-11885037/|title=Notre playlist 2016 : écoutez les 100 chansons de l'année|work=Les Inrocks|access-date=2018-06-04|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceinter.fr/emissions/le-nouveau-rendez-vous/le-nouveau-rendez-vous-22-novembre-2017|title=Le groupe français Rendez-Vous puise dans l'héritage cold-wave pour remettre le post-punk au gout du jour|work=France Inter|access-date=2018-06-05|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceculture.fr/emissions/les-carnets-de-la-creation/elliot-berthault-et-maxime-gendre-musiciens|title=Elliot Berthault et Maxime Gendre, musiciens|work=France Culture|access-date=2018-06-05|language=fr-FR}}</ref>
In 2017, the single "The Others" was used by [[Burger Records]] to represent France for the Burger World Compilation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiepoprock.fr/burger-world-france/|title=Burger World France - Indiepoprock|website=www.indiepoprock.fr|language=fr-FR|access-date=2018-06-11}}</ref>
In June 2018, Rendez-Vous released "Double Zero" extract from their first LP to be released in October.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.noisemag.net/avant-premiere-un-nouveau-morceau-de-rendez-vous-en-ecoute/|title=[Avant-première] Un nouveau morceau de Rendez Vous en écoute|date=2018-06-20|work=New Noise Magazine|access-date=2018-06-20|language=fr-FR}}</ref>
''Superior State,'' the title track of Rendez-Vous' debut album, was released on September 14.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ouilove.co.uk/rendez-vous-superior-state/|title=RENDEZ-VOUS 'Superior State' - Oui Love - New French Music|last=Export|first=Oui Love by Bureau|date=2018-09-14|work=Oui Love - New French Music|access-date=2018-09-18|language=en-GB}}</ref>
On October 24 it's ''Sentimental Animal'' with a video clip in which members of the band appear for the first time. [[Clash (magazine)]] named it track of the day.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/news/track-of-the-day-2410-rendez-vous|title=Track Of The Day 24/10 - Rendez-Vous|work=Clash Magazine|access-date=2018-10-25|language=en}}</ref>
